################################################################################
# Notes
################################################################################

# Auto-generated secrets:
# - If ENCRYPTION_KEY is empty, a 256-bit key will be auto-generated
# - If JWT_SECRET is empty, a secure random secret will be auto-generated
# - If GRAFANA_ADMIN_PASSWORD is empty, a strong password will be auto-generated
# - If DB_PASSWORD is empty, a strong password will be auto-generated
#
# Security Best Practices:
# 1. Use strong, unique passwords (minimum 32 characters)
# 2. Rotate credentials regularly
# 3. Use different API keys for development and production
# 4. Never commit this file to version control
# 5. Restrict file permissions: chmod 600 .secrets
# 6. Use secrets managers (AWS SSM, Azure Key Vault) for production
# 7. Enable audit logging for secret access
# 8. Use SealedSecrets or External Secrets Operator for GitOps
